# 🛡️ RansomShield — Complete Project Explanation (Review Prep)

---

## 1. What Is This Project?

This project is a **ransomware detection system** that identifies ransomware attacks by monitoring **CPU (processor)** and **Disk I/O** activity on a computer. Instead of scanning files for signatures (like a traditional antivirus), it watches *how the computer behaves* internally.

> **Key idea:** Ransomware encrypts files, which creates *unusual patterns* in processor cache events and disk read/write activity. Our system learns these patterns using Machine Learning and flags them in real time.

**Based on the research paper:**
*"Detection of Ransomware Attacks Using Processor and Disk Usage Data"* — Thummapudi et al. (IEEE Access, 2023)

---

## 2. Why This Approach?

| Traditional Antivirus | Our Approach |
|---|---|
| Relies on known signatures/hashes | Detects by **behaviour**, even unknown ransomware |
| Can be evaded by obfuscated malware | Monitors low-level CPU & disk metrics that are hard to fake |
| Needs constant database updates | Trained ML model generalises to new ransomware families |

The paper found that **Hardware Performance Counters (HPCs)** and **Disk I/O stats** change significantly when ransomware runs — even under heavy system workloads.

---

